		<page>
			<exercisegroup cols="2">
				<title>Order of Operations with Whole Numbers</title>
				<introduction>
					<p>
						Use the order of operations to complete each problem. Perform one operation at 
						a time and write the answer in its place. Show each step vertically with an 
						equal sign on each line. There are two examples to show you the proper form:
					</p>
					<p>
						Example A:
						<md>
							<mrow>2 \cdot 3 + 4(7+2) \amp = 2 \cdot 3 + 4(9)</mrow>
							<mrow>\amp = 6 + 36</mrow>
							<mrow>\amp = 42</mrow>
						</md>
					</p>
					<p>
						Example B:
						<md>
							<mrow>\left[10 \div (18 - 16) + 20\right] \div 5 \amp = \left[10 \div 2 + 20\right] \div 5</mrow>
							<mrow>\amp = \left[5 + 20\right] \div 5</mrow>
							<mrow>\amp = 25 \div 5</mrow>
							<mrow>\amp = 5</mrow>
						</md>
					</p>
				</introduction>
				<exercise workspace="1.2in">
					<statement>
						<p>
							<m>16 \div 4 + 7(4)(2)</m>
						</p>
					</statement>
				</exercise>
